gomodel:SYNGO_4775  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3C: \"We established that Nxph4 is indeed glycosylated as its molecular weight was reduced with glycosidase treatment or when all of the four asparagine glycosylation sites were mutated to glutamine (Nxph4-4Q-HA, Figure 3C and D).\"\n\nFigure 3F: Immunoblotting analysis of fractions derived from cerebellar synaptosomal preparation detects Nxph4-3xFLAG in the synaptosomes.\n\nFigure 4: IP+WB on synaptosomes (tissue used: olfactory bulb, hypothalamus, midbrain, hindbrain, and the cerebellum) showed Nxph4 and α-neurexin interact. Reverse-IP on brain lysates.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Mouse cerebral cortices were removed from E16.5 embryos of wild type FVB mice and dissociated\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4775" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

